I do not believe it would be prudent for me to do as the inline comments about the copyright notices suggest. Removing the existing copyright notices would imply that the company I work for (IBM) was the sole author of the software (see also http://opensource.org/faq#preserve-copyright-notices).  On the other hand, my company has very specific standards about when to add copyright notices, for instance when a function or method has been added, so I cannot simply remove the copyright notices I added. Other changes that have been merged contain multiple copyright notices in them (e.g. see https://review.openstack.org/#/c/30479/16), so there appears to be some disagreement about whether or not this is acceptable.
